<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coalition Wins Chair of RAI Watchdog Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coalition Wins Chair of RAI Watchdog Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206203994 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1745 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206203994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There is a piece of good news for the ruling 
coalition. A short time ago, Marco Taradash, a Radical Party 
deputy who ran on a Forza Italia electoral list, was elected 
chairman of the parliamentary watchdog committee on RAI. He 
obtained 22 votes, besting the challenge of the left-wing 
candidate, Mauro Paisan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

