<H3> <TI>   Corfu EU Summit Will Not Deal With FYROM </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Corfu EU Summit Will Not Deal With FYROM </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0206122394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0206122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The issue of Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia--FYROM], and specifically the appeal against Greece at 
the European Court on 14 June for the embargo against Skopje, is 
not on the agenda of the EU [European Union] Summit in Corfu. 
This was stated today by Government Spokesman Evangelos 
Venizelos, who clarified that from the moment the EU Commission 
chose to deal with the issue as a legal one, it has lost its 
political character. As a result, he said, it does not relate 
to the EU Summit. 
  Matthew Nimetz, U.S. special envoy on the Skopje issue, will 
come to Athens next week for contacts with the foreign 
ministry's political leadership. 

</TEXT>

