<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Konstandinos Karamanlis today said that 
what happens in relations among states can not be explained 
logically, as these relations are ruled by absurdity and 
anarchy. The president said an example of the above is the 
Greek-Albanian relations which are ruled by absurdity. 
  Furthermore, the president refused to comment on the 
elections for the European Parliament, citing his office, but he 
indirectly advised fewer statements. He said that he prefers to 
remain quiet when everybody else is talking. 

