<H3> <TI>   DPRK Envoy on Withdrawal From NPT </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Envoy on Withdrawal From NPT </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0306121694 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 3 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0306121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Makoto Otsuka] </F>
  [Text] Vienna, 2 Jun -- Councilor Yun Ho-chin of the DPRK 
(North Korean) Embassy in Vienna said to an ASAHI SHIMBUN 
reporter on 2 June that "we will be obliged to cancel the 
special stand (that we are holding back our decision to withdraw 
from the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT] if economic 
sanctions are imposed." In this way, he disclosed the DPRK's 
intention to officially withdraw from the NPT as soon as 
sanctions are imposed on the DPRK. 
  Meanwhile, the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) 
authorities disclosed on 2 June the fact that North Korea 
continued to remove fuel rods from an experimental reactor in 
Yongbyon on the same day as well. Moreover, it is said that 
North Korea still has not responded to a technological proposal 
which the IAEA made on 31 May regarding fuel rod inspections. 

</TEXT>

