<F P=106> [Article signed PVB: "Libyan Embassy Can Resume Payments </F>
Through Banks"] 
  [Excerpt] Following a decision by the Belgian Government, 
the Libyan Embassy in Brussels can now freely resume regular 
payments of its current expenses through banks. This was made 
possible after negotiations between the Belgian Foreign and 
Finance Ministries and after it was decided at the 27 May 
cabinet meeting to issue a ministerial order exempting the 
embassy from complicated procedures to pay for its transactions. 
[passage omitted] 

