<H3> <TI>   UN To Cancel Talks If Serb Withdrawal Not Complete </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN To Cancel Talks If Serb Withdrawal Not Complete </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306193794 Paris AFP in English 1928 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0306193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, June 3 (AFP) -- The United Nations Friday 
[3 June] warned it would cancel scheduled peace talks on 
Saturday if Bosnian Serb forces did not fully withdraw from 
around Gorazde in eastern Bosnia. 
  Talks on a truce should have begun here Thursday, but 
Bosnian 
Moslems refused to attend so long as Bosnian Serbs continued to 
occupy the UN-declared exclusion zone around Gorazde from which 
they had promised to pull out. 

</TEXT>

