<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Ambassador Says Peace Talks Set To Resume </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnian Ambassador Says Peace Talks Set To Resume </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0606090894 Paris AFP in English 0855 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0606090894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, June 6 (AFP) -- Peace talks on 
Bosnia-Herzegovina were set to resume here Monday morning [6 
June], Bosnian Government Ambassador Mohammed Sacirbey said. 
  "All conditions are met. Negotiations on an overall 
ceasefire will proceed this morning," he told reporters. 
  The mostly Moslem Bosnian government had earlier rejected a 
resumption of talks because of the failure by armed Serbs to 
withdraw from a three-kilometer (two-mile) radius area around 
the east Bosnian town of Gorazde, in defiance of UN demands. 

</TEXT>

