<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ariane Flights Resume, 64th Launch Scheduled for 4 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ariane Flights Resume, 64th Launch Scheduled for 4 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0206141794 Paris LA TRIBUNE DESFOSSES in French 2 Jun 94 p 
9 </F>

<F P=103> BR0206141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LA TRIBUNE DESFOSSES </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The steering committee of the Qualification 
Commission, set up after the failure of the European Ariane 
rocket in January, has given the go-ahead to the resumption of 
flights and confirmed the launch of an Ariane rocket on 
Saturday, 4 June. After a four-month interruption, the 64th 
Ariane is scheduled for launch this Saturday at 0402 (0902 Paris 
time [0702 GMT]) from the Guiana Space Center in Kourou. It 
will carry three satellites: Intelsat- 702, the second of the 
Intelsat-VII series of the international communications 
satellite organization Intelsat, and two scientific 
microsatellites of the British Defense Ministry, the STRV-1A and 
STRV-1B. As a result of the 24 January Ariane failure, which 
was caused by a problem in the turbopump which has now been 
solved, two telecommunications satellites were lost: Turksat-1A 
and Eutelsat-II-F5. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

