<H3> <TI>   Haider Cancels Appearances in Germany </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Haider Cancels Appearances in Germany </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306114894 Vienna DER STANDARD in German 3 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU0306114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DER STANDARD </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [APA report: "Haider Cancels Appearances in FRG"] </F>
  [Text] Munich -- The German "League of Free Citizens" has 
canceled election campaign rallies with its Chairman Manfred 
Brunner and Freedom Party of Austria Chairman Joerg Haider in 
several German cities. On Thursday [2 June] League Spokesman 
Michael Schwilk justified the cancellation by pointing to the 
"massive threat" by "chaotic leftists." One does not want 
"deliberately to get involved in new riots," Schwilk said. 
Brunner and Haider had been attacked in Hamburg with paint bags 
and eggs. 
  Only in Bavaria can one "still feel relatively safe." Haider 
and Brunner's election rally in Munich, which is planned for 
next Sunday, is to go ahead as planned. 

</TEXT>

