<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Aid Salvage of Komsomolets Submarine </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Aid Salvage of Komsomolets Submarine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306121594 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Netherlands is prepared to contribute a million 
dollars to a salvage operation for the Russian nuclear submarine 
Komsomolets in order to prevent an ecological disaster. The 
Komsomolets sank five years ago in the Barents Sea. It is 
rusting so quickly that there is a danger of plutonium being 
released from the wreckage this year. 
  The Netherlands has already had extensive talks with Russia 
about the nature and the costs of a salvage operation. If the 
two countries agree, the Dutch salvage companies Smit 
Internationale and Heerema Offshore will both be involved in the 
operation. 

</TEXT>

