<H3> <TI>   Kohl Addresses Election Rally in Brandenburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Addresses Election Rally in Brandenburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406180394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1724 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0406180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brandenburg (DDP/ADN) -- Federal Chancellor 
Helmut Kohl [Christian Democratic Union -- CDU] today affirmed 
his vision of "flourishing scenes" in the five new laender. At 
a CDU election campaign rally in Brandenburg, Kohl said that his 
prediction of five years [for the eastern laender to catch up 
with the west] could perhaps stretch to "seven or eight, but 
basically I have not been mistaken." At the same time the 
chancellor called for more tolerance between west and east 
Germans, since the people in the two parts of Germany had gone 
through different developments in the past 40 years. 
  In his speech, which was disrupted repeatedly by applause 
and 
whistling, Kohl said that safeguarding peace and freedom and 
fighting mass unemployment were the most important objectives of 
European unification. Kohl also called for joint European 
efforts to solve the asylum problem and combat international 
crime. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

