<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rostock (DDP/ADN) -- The FDP [Free Democratic Party] 
this morning approved its electoral program for the Bundestag 
election in October. In it, the liberals are recommending 
themselves to the voters as the party of achievement and 
committed defenders of the market economy. At the same time, 
the FDP deliberately took a position of liberal independence 
from its CDU/CSU [Christian Democratic Union/Christian Social 
Union] coalition partner in the areas of domestic and social 
policy and foreigners' affairs. 
  The vast majority of the delegates voted in Rostock for the 
program; three voted against and there were three abstentions. 

