<H3> <TI>   Scharping Views Possible Coalition With FDP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Scharping Views Possible Coalition With FDP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406124394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1145 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0406124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hamburg (DDP/ADN) -- The SPD [Social Democratic 
Party of Germany] leader, Rudolf Scharping, does not rule out a 
coalition with the liberals [Free Democratic Party] after the 
Bundestag election, even after the FDP decided at its party 
conference in favor of a coalition with the CDU/CSU Union. The 
FDP had "not said that if the Union had a poor election result, 
it would go into opposition," Scharping told BILD AM SONNTAG 
newspaper. On the eve of the elections, the "supply of partners 
will be greater than the demand." 
  At the same time, he once again rejected the idea of a grand 
coalition. The goal of the Social Democrats was to become the 
strongest party: "We will always find a partner in that event," 
Scharping added. "Exclusive rights for small parties" could not 
be arranged with him. [passage omitted] 

