<H3> <TI>   CDU/CSU Leads SPD by 42 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CDU/CSU Leads SPD by 42 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0506193294 Hamburg BILD in German 4 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0506193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "CDU Overtakes SPD"] </F>
  [Text] Bonn -- With 42 percent (last week: 39 percent), 
the Christian Democratic Union [CDU]/Christian Social Union 
[CSU] has for the first time overtaken the Social Democratic 
Party of Germany [SPD] with 39 percent (40 percent). The Free 
Democratic Party of Germany [FDP] gains 4 percent (6 percent), 
the Alliance 90/Greens 10 percent (8 percent), the Republikaner 
1 percent (3 percent), and the Party of Democratic Socialism 
[PDS] 2 percent, again. Thirty-five percent (32 percent) want 
Kohl as chancellor and, as before, 32 percent want SPD candidate 
Scharping (Forsa poll). 

</TEXT>

