<H3> <TI>   3,000 Demonstrate in Northeim Against FAP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    3,000 Demonstrate in Northeim Against FAP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406172594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1641 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0406172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Northeim (DDP/ADN) -- Approximately 3,000 people 
attended a demonstration against the right-wing Free German 
Workers' Party (FAP) in Northeim/Lower Saxony today. Clashes 
between demonstrators and police, in which several people were 
injured, occurred late this afternoon at the police cordon 
outside the home of Thorsten Heise, the chairman of the Lower 
Saxony and Saxony-Anhalt regional association, who was arrested 
on Thursday [2 June]. [passage omitted] 
  Twenty-four-year-old Heise has previous convictions and is 
considered the brains behind many violent actions carried out by 
right-wing extremists. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

