<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Ban Turkish Rally, Fear Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Ban Turkish Rally, Fear Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306153994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1431 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DDP/ADN) -- The Hamburg police have banned 
a demonstration planned for Saturday [4 June] by left-wing 
Turkish groups outside the Turkish Consulate General because 
clashes are feared. Police stated today that several Turkish and 
Kurdish organizations have announced their participation in the 
demonstration against the deportation of Iranian asylum-seekers 
from Turkey to Iran. The ban is extended to substitute 
demonstrations which have not yet been registered. 
  The ban has been imposed against the background of the 
serious clashes between left- and right-wing Turks last weekend 
when four people were injured. Three arson attacks were carried 
out on Turkish establishments on Sunday, which police assume 
were connected to the clashes. 

</TEXT>

