  [Excerpt] According to the latest extensive poll from 
Statistics Sweden, the Social Democrats still have a big lead in 
front of the government parties. The Social Democrats will get 
50.1 percent, the Party of the Left 3.9 percent, the Moderates 
21.8 percent, the Liberal Party 6.7 percent, the Center 7.9 
percent, Christian Democratic Party 4.4 percent, New Democracy 
2.3 percent, and the Greens 2.6 percent. The parties that have 
increased their support compared to November last year are the 
Moderates and the Center, while New Democracy has gone down by 3 
percent. [passage omitted] 

