<H3> <TI>   Lamassoure Meets With Kosovo's Rugova </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lamassoure Meets With Kosovo's Rugova </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306164194 Paris AFP in English 1618 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0306164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] PARIS, June 3 (AFP) -- The president of the 
opposition Democratic League of Kosovo, Ibrahim Rugova, was 
received Friday [3 June] in Paris by French Minister for 
European Affairs Alain Lamassoure, the French Foreign Ministry 
said. 
  The Ministry said the meeting underlined the attention Paris 
was paying to the situation in Kosovo, a Serb-administered 
province but whose population almost exclusively comprises 
ethnic Albanians. 
  Lamassoure said France favoured a policy of dialogue between 
communities in the province along with respect for human rights. 
  He added Paris supported internationally-recognised autonomy 
for Kosovo, which had been repealed by Belgrade in 1989. 
  Rugova told a press conference Thursday he hoped France 
would 
back the idea of establishing a United Nations protectorate in 
Kosovo, in line with a plan he proposed to the world body early 
last year. 

</TEXT>

