<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Urges International Forum, Russian Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Urges International Forum, Russian Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0506143694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1400 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0506143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Cyprus Government is working toward convening 
an international conference on the Cyprus issue. This statement 
was made by Foreign Minister at Larnaca Airport shortly before 
his departure this afternoon on an official visit to Moscow. He 
said that the Cyprus Government believes that convening an 
international conference is a very serious proposal, since the 
initiatives taken in the Cyprus issue thus far have failed. He 
added: For this reason, we must address the substance of the 
problem, which is nothing less than the presence of occupation 
troops and settlers in Cyprus. Mr. Mikhailidhis noted: If some 
countries agree or disagree, we will see this in the course of 
things. The foreign minister further said: In any case, we 
will work toward this. 
  The Cyprus issue will be the basic topic of Mr. 
Mikhailidhis' 
talks in Moscow and, as he noted, there will also be discussion 
of the Russian suggestions included in the options cited in the 
UN secretary general's report. He stressed that the Cyprus 
Government attaches great importance to his visit to Moscow for 
two important reasons: First, because of Russia's noteworthy 
active role on the international political scene and, second, 
because of its strong interest in Cyprus. He added: Russia's 
role will be very decisive in view of the consultations at the 
Security Council on the options to be adopted for the 
continuation of the peace process in Cyprus. 

</TEXT>

