<H3> <TI>   Turkey's Ulucevik Ends Visit; Rejects Pressure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkey's Ulucevik Ends Visit; Rejects Pressure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0306165994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1555 GMT 3 Jul 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0306165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lefkosa [Nicosia], June 3 (AA) -- Foreign Ministry 
Deputy Undersecretary Tugay Ulucevik, on Friday [3 June] said 
that the Cyprus problem cannot be solved by forceful means or 
pressure methods. 
  "Turkey is determined to prevent any kind of pressure 
directed against the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus," he 
said. 
  Ulucevik on Friday concluded his talks on the island and 
left 
for Turkey. 
  Speaking to reporters before his departure at Ercan [Tymbou] 
Airport, he said that the Turkish side has shown necessary 
goodwill and sacrifice during the talks process for the 
UN-proposed confidence building measures package. 
  He also criticized the UN secretary general's report which 
he 
added does not take into consideration the constructive attitude 
of the Turkish side. 

</TEXT>

