<F P=103> NC0606151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkish President Suleyman Demirel has sent a letter 
to President Konstandinos Karamanlis. Government Spokesman 
Evangelos Venizelos confirmed that the letter has been sent, but 
he is not yet aware of its contents. 
  The letter reportedly refers to issues of the Workers Party 
of Kurdistan. Referring to Turkish claims that Kurdish 
guerrillas are being trained in Greece, the spokesman explicitly 
reiterated that such claims are slanderous and unfounded. He 
added that the Greek position is well-known, and mentioned the 
case of the Kurd who was arrested in Turkey and, after being 
tortured, supposedly confessed about the training of Kurds in 
Greece. 

