<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Talks on FYROM Convene in Athens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Talks on FYROM Convene in Athens </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Spokesman Discusses UN Report </H4>

<F P=102> NC0306185094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306185094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali called on 
special envoy Cyrus Vance to move as quickly as possible to a 
new round of negotiations with Athens and Skopje [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM]. ATHENS NEWS AGENCY 
reports from UN Headquarters in New York that Butrus-Ghali's 
request to Vance is included in a two-page report the UN 
secretary general submitted to the Security Council. In his 
report, Butrus-Ghali underlines that Vance's mediating mission 
is not affected by the European Court case of the Greek 
countermeasures against Skopje. The UN secretary general notes 
that he will submit a new report to the Security Council after 
the 13 June meetings in New York between Vance and the 
representatives of Greece and Skopje. 
  Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today described 
Butrus-Ghali's report to the Security Council on the issue of 
Skopje as brief, typical, and descriptive. Venizelos said he 
considers the secretary general's note that there is a need to 
continue the Vance initiative for solution of the issue as 
important. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

