<H4>    Samaras Rejects Double Name </H4>

<F P=102> NC0606152994 Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 6 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC0606152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Yesterday Political Spring Chairman Andonios 
Samaras once again asked the Greek Government to bring the issue 
of Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] to 
the European Union [EU] Summit in Corfu. At the same time, he 
called on the government to capitalize on the Greek presidency 
and to deal with the problems faced by farmers and the amendment 
of the Common Agriculture Policy. 
  Samaras was also asked about reports of U.S. Envoy Matthew 
Nimetz's proposal for a double name for Skopje. He said: 
"There should be an immediate and categorical rejection by the 
government." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

