<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Welcomes Oxman Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Welcomes Oxman Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306184994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos described 
as positive the statement by Stephen Oxman, U.S. assistant 
secretary of state for European affairs, that human rights in 
Albania are somewhat violated lately. Venizelos justified his 
description of Oxman's statement by saying that the latest 
statement improves on the one by State Department Spokesman 
Michael McCurry. McCurry had said the United States has no 
evidence regarding the violation of human rights in Albania. 
Replying to a question, Venizelos said the Greek Government 
believes there is a climate of tension and insecurity which 
insults the human rights of the Greeks of Albania. 

</TEXT>

