<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Begins Talks on Karkuk-Yumurtalik Pipeline </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Begins Talks on Karkuk-Yumurtalik Pipeline </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    U.S. Attitude `Constructive' </H4>

<F P=102> TA0406053794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0430 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0406053794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Progress has been achieved in the talks being held 
in Washington between Turkey and the United States in connection 
with the Karkuk-Yumurtalik oil pipeline. 
  Foreign Ministry Under Secretary Ozdem Sanberk, who is 
holding contacts in Washington in connection with the pipeline, 
has said that the U.S. Administration has quite a constructive 
attitude regarding the matter. He said the U.S. Administration 
told him that the United States will display an attitude in line 
with Turkey's requests at the United Nations. Sanberk stressed 
that Turkey will act while remaining loyal to the UN sanctions 
imposed on Iraq. Encouraging developments are taking place, he 
said, indicating that the oil in the Karkuk-Yumurtalik pipeline 
will be pumped out this year. 
  After Washington, Sanberk will go to New York to discuss 
with 
the permanent representatives at the UN Security Council the 
need to pump out the oil in the pipeline for technical reasons. 

</TEXT>

