<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Holds Contacts in Ankara </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Holds Contacts in Ankara </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0306170694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1610 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0306170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 3 (AA) -- Israel's Minister of 
Economics and Planning, Shim'on Shetrit, currently on an 
official visit in Turkey, on Friday [3 June] met with State 
Minister Aykon Dogan. 
  During meetings between delegations of both countries, both 
sides reiterated mutual wishes that the free trade agreement 
procedure between Turkey and Israel should be finalized in the 
month of July. 
  A meeting on the issue will be held during the third week of 
July. 
  Sources said that discussions still continue concerning this 
agreement which was on the agenda during a recent visit to 
Turkey by Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres on April 10-12, 
between the Israeli Foreign Ministry and Ministries of Industry 
and Trade. 
  Dogan told reporters that Turkey's and Israel's economy are 
of a nature that complement one another adding that Israel 
considers Turkey a country with great potential in the Middle 
East in economic, political and social fields. 
  Dogan also said that a great number of Israeli tourists were 
expected in Turkey in 1994, and Turkey also aims to increase its 
exports to Israel. 
  He added that Israel is also interested in investments in 
industry, tourism, transport and in the irrigation projects in 
Southeastern Anatolian Project (GAP) region. 
  Dogan said that Turkey has a unifying characteristic in the 
region adding, Israeli businessmen have also mentioned such 
projects as entering into joint partnership projects with 
Turkey's experience aiming at the CIS countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

