<H3> <TI>   Official Calls For Action in Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Calls For Action in Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506132294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1422 GMT 
5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0506132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] "The situation is worse than was thought. 
Without a very wide-ranging commitment by a number of 
governments, European and non-European, the Rwandan crisis will 
widen." This was said by the Undersecretary for Foreign Affairs, 
Franco Rocchetta, in Nairobi, where he was brought back by the 
UN plane which was forced to return to the Kenyan capital from 
Rwandan shelling in Kigali. 
  Rocchetta added that the Italian Government must remain 
neutral with regard to both ethnic groups involved in the 
fighting. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

