<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Criticizes `Unfounded Charges' by Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Criticizes `Unfounded Charges' by Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306164894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said Turkey 
continues to carry out a slanderous campaign against Greece and 
to bring unfounded charges by invoking events that are obviously 
contrary to the reality. The spokesman made the above statement 
when he was asked about the government's comment regarding the 
confession of the Kurdish fighter who was tortured by Turkish 
authorities into saying that he had been trained at a camp for 
terrorists in Greece. Venizelos underlined once again that our 
country will not contribute to the effort to cultivate false 
tension. We call on Turkey, the spokesman said, to stop 
implicating Greece in its internal problems. The Greek state 
authority, Venizelos stressed, controls the whole of its 
territory which is open and accessible to everyone, especially 
to journalists. Finally, the government spokesman expressed the 
government's regret for the confirmation of brutal violation of 
human rights, such as in the case of detained persons subjected 
to torture to sign forged confessions. 

</TEXT>

