<H3> <TI>   Kohl, Gonzalez Hold Talks in Schwerin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl, Gonzalez Hold Talks in Schwerin </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Discuss European Currency </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706083494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0759 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706083494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Schwerin (DDP/ADN) -- In the view of Chancellor 
Helmut Kohl, "stability criteria are more important than the 
calendar" for European currency union. Kohl said in Schwerin 
today, during German-Spanish government consultations, that the 
national economies must "reach maturity" as a precondition for 
the planned currency union of the European states. The 
"calendar" for currency union could be postponed, but cannot be 
abandoned, Kohl stressed. 
  Kohl and Spanish Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez are to talk 
further today about the topic of the European currency union. 
Gonzalez pointed out that his two days of talks in Schwerin are 
his first visit to one of the new federal German states. 

</TEXT>

