<H4>    Support European Integration </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706081394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0724 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Schwerin (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
called for consistent continuation of the policy of European 
integration. Following German-Spanish government consultations 
in Schwerin, he said today that to a great degree, European 
integration had contributed to the prosperity and freedom of 
nations. He and his Spanish counterpart Felipe Gonzalez agreed 
to continue to press for the integration of Europe. 
  Kohl went on to say that both sides had agreed during the 
two-day summit in the Mecklenburg-Western Pomeranian capital 
that they would intensively prepare and coordinate in advance 
for the forthcoming European Union Council meeting in Corfu. 
  Against the background of the D-Day celebrations, Kohl said 
Germany has learned the lesson of history. 

</TEXT>

