<H3> <TI>   Fini: Fascism `Cannot Return' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fini: Fascism `Cannot Return' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606150194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1430 GMT 
6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gianfranco Fini [leader of the National Alliance] 
said: "I am happy that [Israeli Foreign Minister] Shim'on Peres 
has said that there is no hostility on the part of the Israeli 
Government toward the Italian Government, and I am convinced 
that the concerns of [European Commission President Jacques] 
Delors will diminish in a short time when everyone has 
understood the values that are guiding both the government and 
the National Alliance." 
  These are the values of "liberty, democracy, social justice, 
and tolerance," Fini explained, "in which all Italians believe." 
Fascism "ended in 1945 and cannot return," and "the National 
Alliance is neither a fascist or neofascist force." 

