<H3> <TI>   Cautionary Warrants Issued to Mediobanca Directors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cautionary Warrants Issued to Mediobanca Directors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005170994 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1600 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] A little less than an hour ago in Milan, the 
finance police entered the headquarters of Mediobanca, the 
temple of Italian financial life. They delivered four 
cautionary warrants. Antonio Graziani reports: 
  [Graziani] Honorary President Enrico Cuccia, Director 
General 
Vincenzo Maranghi, and Directors Maurizio Romiti and Gerardo 
Braggiotti are the Mediobanca directors who received the four 
cautionary warrants issued this afternoon by Ravenna prosecutor 
Francesco Mauro Iacoviello. The news was given with an official 
communique signed by the very same prosecutor who is 
investigating the role played by Mediobanca in the Ferruzzi 
affair. [passage omitted] 
  Although we took into account the ideas put forward by 
Professor Dominioni [Mediobanca lawyer] in his defense document 
and by Professor Trimarchi [Milan law professor] in his 
pro-veritate statement--says the official document issued by the 
Ravenna prosecution office--we think that at this point in the 
investigation we must issue the cautionary warrants in order to 
continue the investigation. 

