<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Danger' From Turkey, Not Turkish Cypriots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Danger' From Turkey, Not Turkish Cypriots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606150694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0606150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said the 
Republic of Cyprus will ask to participate in an international 
conference in Cyprus, if such a meeting is held. The spokesman 
clarified that among the alternatives being discussed include 
convening an international conference and the visit by 
representatives of the five UN Security Council permanent 
members. 
  The Cypriot Government welcomed the reference to the Cyprus 
issue, which is contained in the final resolution of the 
Nonaligned Movement foreign minister's meeting, held in Cairo. 
The spokesman said the resolution contains a series of positive 
points for Cyprus and noted the specific reference to UN 
Security Council Resolutions 365, 541, and 550 and the request 
for an international conference. 
  Commenting on Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas' statement 
about signing a nonaggression pact between the two communities, 
the government spokesman said this would be meaningful if a 
similar treaty would also be signed between Cyprus and Turkey. 
He added that the fear and danger comes from Turkey, which 
holds part of Cyprus, not from the Turkish Cypriot community. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

