<H3> <TI>   Papoulias Briefing Rejects FYROM Scenarios </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papoulias Briefing Rejects FYROM Scenarios </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606175494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0606175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias today briefed 
President Konstandinos Karamanlis on foreign policy issues, 
particularly the progress of our national issues, as well as on 
the results of his recent visit to Moscow. After the meeting, 
Papoulias told correspondents that the president has a personal 
interest in the issues they discussed. 
  Furthermore, Papoulias said the latest scenarios about a 
double or triple name for Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia -- FYROM] are not realistic. He added that the 
Greek side does not have any particular expectations from the 
visit of U.S. Presidential Envoy Matthew Nimetz. The U.S. 
President's special envoy, Papoulias said, came to Greece to 
sound out the Greek Government and relay its views on the 
national issue to Skopje. On Nimetz's visit, Papoulias said: 
When there is a negotiation on some ideas, there should be an 
effort by the negotiators. This is logical. If this effort 
were at a standstill, then Nimetz would not have come to Athens. 
  Papoulias concluded by saying that he will be holding a news 
conference after his meeting with Nimetz to provide more details 
on the issue. 

</TEXT>

