<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Forced Solution Unacceptable </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Forced Solution Unacceptable </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0406053894 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0430 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0406053894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has said that the UN 
secretary general's Cyprus report is prejudiced. 
  Cetin was replying to reporters' questions at Ankara 
Esenboga 
Airport on his return from visits to Ukraine and Moldova last 
night. He stressed that a forced solution will never be accepted 
in Cyprus. He added: The UN attitude is one of forcing one of 
the sides -- the Turkish Cypriot side -- to accept the package 
the other side accepts. A forced solution will never be 
accepted. In that case, there would be no solution. 
  Cetin stressed that the fact that there exist two sides on 
the island must be accepted. He pointed out that Denktas' 
contribution in turning the Vienna talks into a forward step is 
an important development. 

</TEXT>

