<H3> <TI>   Thai Foreign Minister Sunsiri Makes Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Thai Foreign Minister Sunsiri Makes Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Cetin </H4>

<F P=102> TA0406131394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 
GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0406131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Thai Foreign Minister Prasong Sunsiri, who arrived 
in Ankara on an official visit yesterday, has begun his 
contacts. He met with Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin this 
morning. Later, the official Turkish-Thai talks were held. 
  In a statement at the meeting, Cetin said that geographic 
distances no longer affect relations between nations. Pointing 
out that Turkey and Thailand are two countries with significant 
economic power in their respective regions, Cetin added: We 
will discuss ways in which we can cooperate in the economic 
field and the two countries can combine their respective 
influences in their regions. There might be significant 
developments in the field of tourism. We can also develop our 
cultural and trade relations. 
  Recalling that Sunsiri arrived in Turkey after attending the 
Nonaligned conference in Egypt, Cetin added that Sunsiri will 
brief him on that conference and that various regional problems 
will be discussed. 
  President Suleyman Demirel also received Sunsiri at the 
Cankaya Mansion today. 

</TEXT>

