<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Wants Death Penalty for Hezbollah Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106195294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Excerpt] The state has filed charges against 35 members 
of the terror organization known to the public as the Hezbollah. 
According to information received from Bekir Selcuk, public 
prosecutor of the Diyarbakir State Security Court, the 
indictment demands the death penalty for 15 of the suspects, 
15-year prison terms for three of the suspects, and prison terms 
ranging from 10 to 15 years for the remaining 17 suspects. The 
36-page indictment notes that in accordance with Article 125 of 
the Turkish Penal Code, 15 of the suspects are accused of 
engaging in activities aimed at establishing a Kurdish state 
based on Islamic principles in southeastern Anatolia. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

