<H3> <TI>   Government Supports Extending `Provide Comfort' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Supports Extending `Provide Comfort' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0606173194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0606173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the National Security Council </F>
Secretariat General on 6 June] 
  [Text] The National Security Council [NSC] held an 
extraordinary session at the Cankaya Presidential Mansion on 6 
June under the chairmanship of President Suleyman Demirel, with 
the participation of the prime minister, the chief of the 
General Staff, NSC member ministers, the force commanders, the 
general commander of the Gendarmerie, and the secretary general 
of the NSC. The state minister and deputy prime minister also 
attended the meeting. 
  The developments in northern Iraq within the context of 
Operation Provide Comfort were discussed during the meeting. 
The NSC determined that the conditions in the region have not 
reached the point that call for the termination of the said 
operation. In view of this situation and in light of the 
importance of protecting Iraq's territorial integrity, the NSC 
decided to recommend to the government to extend the mandate of 
the multinational force as of 30 June for a period to be deemed 
appropriate. 

</TEXT>

