<H3> <TI>   Waigel Urges Prague To Repeal Benes Decrees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Waigel Urges Prague To Repeal Benes Decrees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0406175194 Hamburg DPA in German 1444 GMT 4 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0406175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Neusaess (DPA) -- Christian Social Union [CSU] 
Chairman Theo Waigel on Saturday [4 June] called on the Czech 
Government to dissociate itself from the "Benes decrees that are 
contrary to international law" and to repeal them. The decrees 
signed by Czechoslovak President Eduard Benes after the end of 
World War II were the legal basis for the expropriation and 
expulsion of many Sudeten Germans. 
  Waigel, who addressed 660 members of the CSU working group 
"Union of Expellees" in Neusaess near Augsburg, dealt with the 
wish of East European states to become members of the European 
Union (EU). The CSU is "open to it." However, as Waigel 
further stressed, these states would also have to be prepared to 
accept the European legal system with the relevant law on ethnic 
groups and expellees. 
  As spokesman of the Sudeten German ethnic group, Franz 
Neubauer stressed that the right to one's homeland includes the 
right to return. "It is not decisive how many will really make 
use of it." 

</TEXT>

