<H3> <TI>   Youths Detained at Kohl Rally in Brandenburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Youths Detained at Kohl Rally in Brandenburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0406194294 Hamburg DPA in German 1737 GMT 4 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0406194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brandenburg (DPA) -- Approximately 10 adolescents 
were temporarily detained at a rally with Chancellor Helmut Kohl 
(Christian Democratic Union) in the Havel city of Brandenburg on 
Saturday evening [4 June]. Some of them had broken through a 
barrier and loudly protested against the chancellor's speech. 
  At the rally with 5,000 participants, Kohl had called for 
participation in building a joint European home. Only the 
"United States of Europe" guarantees peace and freedom, Kohl 
stated in his speech one week before the European elections. 
His comments were accompanied by violent booing and a chorus of 
whistles. On banners, citizens opposed the expulsion of eastern 
Germans from their plots. 
  The chancellor said that the reduction of unemployment is 
the 
greatest challenge of the country's community of solidarity. 
Unemployment will not disappear overnight, but it can be warded 
off. At the same time, Kohl admitted mistakes in shaping German 
unity and substantiated them by a lack of experience. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

